            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3EAmos%201%3A1-3%3A15%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22amos_1_1%22%20bk%3D%22amos%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EAmos%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20message%20was%20given%20to%20Amos%2C%20a%20shepherd%20from%20the%20town%20of%20Tekoa%20in%20Judah.%20He%20received%20this%20message%20in%20visions%20two%20years%20before%20the%20earthquake%2C%20when%20Uzziah%20was%20king%20of%20Judah%20and%20Jeroboam%26%23xA0%3BII%2C%20the%20son%20of%20Jehoash%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E1%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EJoash%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Jehoash.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20was%20king%20of%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22amos_1_2%22%20bk%3D%22amos%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20is%20what%20he%20saw%20and%20heard%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1-sp%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BThe%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20voice%20will%20roar%20from%20Zion%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Eand%20thunder%20from%20Jerusalem!%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1%22%3EThe%20lush%20pastures%20of%20the%20shepherds%20will%20dry%20up%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Ethe%20grass%20on%20Mount%20Carmel%20will%20wither%20and%20die.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22amos_1_3%22%20bk%3D%22amos%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EGod%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Judgment%20on%20Israel%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Neighbors%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20is%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20says%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1-sp%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BThe%20people%20of%20Damascus%20have%20sinned%20again%20and%20again%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E1%3A3%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ehave%20committed%20three%20sins%2C%20even%20four%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20in%201%3A6%2C%209%2C%2011%2C%2013.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Eand%20I%20will%20not%20let%20them%20go%20unpunished!%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1%22%3EThey%20beat%20down%20my%20people%20in%20Gilead%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Eas%20grain%20is%20threshed%20with%20iron%20sledges.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22amos_1_4%22%20bk%3D%22amos%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1-vn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20I%20will%20send%20down%20fire%20on%20King%20Hazael%26%23x2019%3Bs%20palace%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Eand%20the%20fortresses%20of%20King%20Ben-hadad%20will%20be%20destroyed.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22amos_1_5%22%20bk%3D%22amos%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1-vn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EI%20will%20break%20down%20the%20gates%20of%20Damascus%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Eand%20slaughter%20the%20people%20in%20the%20valley%20of%20Aven.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1%22%3EI%20will%20destroy%20the%20ruler%20in%20Beth-eden%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Eand%20the%20people%20of%20Aram%20will%20go%20as%20captives%20to%20Kir%2C%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Esays%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22amos_1_6%22%20bk%3D%22amos%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-fl-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20is%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20says%3A%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1-sp%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BThe%20people%20of%20Gaza%20have%20sinned%20again%20and%20again%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Eand%20I%20will%20not%20let%20them%20go%20unpunished!%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1%22%3EThey%20sent%20whole%20villages%20into%20exile%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Eselling%20them%20as%20slaves%20to%20Edom.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22amos_1_7%22%20bk%3D%22amos%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1-vn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20I%20will%20send%20down%20fire%20on%20the%20walls%20of%20Gaza%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Eand%20all%20its%20fortresses%20will%20be%20destroyed.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22amos_1_8%22%20bk%3D%22amos%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1-vn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EI%20will%20slaughter%20the%20people%20of%20Ashdod%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Eand%20destroy%20the%20king%20of%20Ashkelon.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1%22%3EThen%20I%20will%20turn%20to%20attack%20Ekron%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Eand%20the%20few%20Philistines%20still%20left%20will%20be%20killed%2C%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Esays%20the%20Sovereign%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22amos_1_9%22%20bk%3D%22amos%22%20ch%3D%221%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-fl-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20is%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20says%3A%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1-sp%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BThe%20people%20of%20Tyre%20have%20sinned%20again%20and%20again%2